RACE.RACE_TEXT: PARX RACING RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Horses entered for the PA Bred Waiver will carry the age specified weight plus 3 additional lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ISLAND BELLE settled close up inside, angled out advancing into the stretch and rallied clear under urging. FANCY SCEPTER set the pace, repelled challenges, was collared into the stretch and faltered. WILDCAT GIRL prompted the pace outside, bid on the final turn then proved empty in the stretch. ELEVENMONTHSLATER trailed early, advanced outside and was no threat. TEMPEST RISING saved ground off the leaders and gave way readily. END OF THE RAINBOW lacked speed and stopped abruptly losing contact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PARX RACING RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 24000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 14 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PORSUPUESTO raced off the rail, off the pace, made a four wide run on the turn, rallied outside rivals, put a head in front at the eighth pole, then dug in gamely outside of AVA K'S BOY, dueled with that rival to the wire and prevailed. AVA K'S BOY raced off the pace, moved up inside on the turn, bid between rivals at the quarter pole, dug in gamely inside in the final furlong, dueled to the wire and just missed. BIG BROWN SHOES vied between rivals early, then stalked the pace, bid on the turn, came three wide into the lane and weakened. JOVIAL vied inside for the early lead, then took over to set the pace, dueled on the turn and weakened. FULL CONTACT chased on the inside and tired. STRAWBERRY CONE vied outside for the early lead, then stalked outside, chased on the turn and tired. RUTHENIAN raced off the pace inside and did not factor. WHERESTHEPASSION was steadied at the start, raced off the pace, moved up three wide on the turn, then gave way.

Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 14 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOOPLA set pressured pace in the two path, repelled rivals and stayed safe under steady handling. ICONIC LEGACY broke very slowly, rushed to contention wide and continued gamely to the finish. ABUELO NUNO raced inside behind the dueling pacesetters then made a gradual late gain. RUFFY prompted pace along the inside then weakened slightly in the stretch. DOCTOR DOOM saved ground early, moved outside on the turn and was no threat. HOTPOT was fractious in the gate then lunged at the start losing best chance and chased wide.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PARX RACING RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 30000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Horses entered for the PA Bred Waiver will carry the age specified weight plus 3 additional lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NINTH OF APRIL set the pace on the inside, dueled with GOLDEN WILDCAT on the turn, responded when roused, pulled away and was kept to the task. GOLDEN WILDCAT vied three wide early, then pressed the pace, bid on the turn, dueled outside of the winner, could not stay with that rival and remained clear for the place spot. AMERICAN DAY vied two wide early, then stalked, chased two wide on the turn, lacked a bid and finished evenly. LT'S JACKNTHEBOX stalked outside, chased three wide on the turn and lacked a rally. JUNGLHERLY LOVE raced off the pace inside, chased inside on the turn, steadied in tight at the quarter pole and lacked a rally. PRINCIPE was outrun.
